<% article_link = article_url("path-guiding-blender-interior-renders") %>
<% image_style = "display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; border: 0; border-radius: 4px;" %>

<p>
  hey <%= @subscriber.greeting_name %>,
</p>

<p>
  Here's an interesting render setting not many people know about:
  <a href="<%= article_link %>">Path Guiding</a>
</p>

<p>
  I wrote an article about how it can help optimise render times:
</p>

<figure style="margin: 0 0 1.5em; text-align: center;">
  <a href="<%= article_link %>">
    <img src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/uQvhNndPG90/maxresdefault.jpg"
         alt="Blender Path Guiding" width="600" style="<%= image_style %>">
  </a>
  <figcaption style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 14px; color: #555555;">
    Optimize Your Interior Renders
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>
  I've also figured out a way to measure noise in a render, and used it on an
  interior scene.<br>
  In the tests, Path Guiding leads to a <strong>37% reduction in render
  time!</strong>
</p>

<figure style="margin: 0 0 1.5em; text-align: center;">
  <a href="<%= article_link %>">
    <img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/blendergrid/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto,w_1200/articles/path-guiding-blender-interior-renders/path-guiding-render-time-vs-noise"
         alt="Render time vs. noise: Path Guiding reduced render time by 37%"
         width="600" style="<%= image_style %>">
  </a>
</figure>

<p>
  Pretty cool tech.
</p>

<p>
  Unfortunately Path Guiding is only available on the CPU right now. I heard there
  are plans to make it work on GPUs as well though.
</p>

<p>
  If you're rendering with Blendergrid, it's still relevant, because we mainly use
  large CPU servers.
</p>

<p>
  I hope you enjoy the <a href="<%= article_link %>">article</a>!
</p>

<p>
  Cheers,<br>
  Richard
</p>

<%= render "footer" %>
